# Auth Rules

## Stack

- Supabase Auth (JWT Bearer). Profile `role` and `avatar_url` from `profiles` table.
- Middleware: `@src/middleware/auth.ts` — `requireAuth`, `optionalAuth`, `requireRole(...)`.
- Role types and hierarchy: `@src/types/roles.ts` (`isAtLeastRole`).

## Roles (low → high)

`guest` < `user` < `author` < `author_plus` < `super_author` < `admin`

- Default for authenticated users without profile role: `user`.
- API project/glossary/export routes typically use `requireRole('author')`.
- Admin routes use `requireRole('admin')`.

## Client gates

- `AuthorGate` — author+ routes under `/projects/*`
- `AdminGate` — `/admin/entities`
- Guests hitting protected paths → redirect `/?login=required`

## Cache

- Auth profile cached in memory + Redis (`CACHE_PREFIX.authProfile`). Invalidate on profile/avatar updates per `@.cursor/rules/cache.mdc`.

## When changing auth

- Update `@src/middleware/auth.ts`, affected routes in `@src/server.ts`, and client gates if paths change.
- Update route map in `@.cursor/rules/routing.mdc` if access levels change.
